 Elliotdale - Police in Elliotdale arrested a 39-year-old man for possession of unlicensed firearm and ammunition on Sunday. "The suspect was arrested at Nkanya Village, Elliotdale," said police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha. "The firearm will be sent for ballistic testing to establish if it was used in the commission of crime around Elliotdale and the surrounding areas. "The suspect will appear before the Elliotdale Magistrate’s Court on Monday on charges of possession of unlicensed firearm and ammunition." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 